This directory contains files that provide DNSSEC validation to the sendmail
Mail Tranfer Agent.

[1]
The spfmilter-1.0.8_dnssec_patch.txt file contains a patch to spfmilter-1.0.8
that provides DNSSEC validation.  It uses API from libspf2 with the
dnssec_patch applied (see ../README).

spfmilter-1.0.8 can be downloaded from http://www.libspf2.org/download.html

To apply this patch, download spfmilter-1.0.8.tar.gz from the above website.
Unzip and untar it by:

	tar -xvzf spfmilter-1.0.8.tar.gz

Go to the spfmilter-1.0.8 directory:

	cd spfmilter-1.0.8

Now apply the above patch by:

	patch -p 0 -b -z .orig </path/to/patch/spfmilter-1.0.8_dnssec_patch.txt

This will apply the patch and store the original files with a .orig suffix.

Configure, compile and install libspf2 as per the instructions given in the
spfmilter-1.0.8 distribution.

[2]
The other files in this directory provide a dnssec-milter that validates the
sending MTA.  These files are obsolete and may be deleted in future.
